section.section:
Consent to guardianship is not valid unless the consent:
is given after the child for whom guardianship is sought is born;
is given in a language that the party understands;
if given in a language other than English:
contains an express notice of:
is accompanied by an affidavit of counsel appointed under § 5-3A-07(a) of this subtitle stating that a parent who is a minor or has a disability consents knowingly and voluntarily.

text.section:
If a petitioner becomes aware, before a court rules on a petition, that a condition of consent under § 5-3A-18(b) of this subtitle cannot be fulfilled, the petitioner promptly shall:
file notice with the court;
give notice to all of the other parties;
if consent was received from a governmental unit or person who is not a party, give notice to that unit or person; and
if the unit or person enters into a new consent, file the consent with the court; or
if the unit or person fails to enter into a new consent, dismiss the petition.
